Create a Facebook Messenger Channel in Service Cloud

To control how incoming messages are routed, link an Omni-Channel flow or routing configuration to your Facebook Messenger channel.

Available in: Lightning Experience.
This article applies to: Standard and enhanced Facebook Messenger channels.

USER PERMISSIONS NEEDED:
To set up Messaging: Configure Messaging
To view Facebook Messenger channels: View Setup and Configuration
To create Facebook Messenger channels: System Administrator AND Configure Messaging

OR
Configure Messaging AND Customize Application AND Manage Auth. Providers AND View Setup and Configuration AND Modify All Data

Before you start, you need a Facebook account, Facebook username and password, and a Facebook page.

From Setup in Lightning Experience, enter Messaging in the Quick Find box, and select Messaging Settings.
In the Channels section, click New Channel | Start | Facebook Messenger.
Choose a channel type of Enhanced (recommended) or standard.
Follow the prompts to log into Facebook and select a Facebook page to use with Messaging.
Click Next.
In the Chat Acknowledgment field, enter a message that’s sent in response to a customer’s initial message.
Click Next.
Choose how to route incoming messages to agents.
